#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:5
msgid "Devlink Shared Instances"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:8
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:10
msgid ""
"Shared devlink instances allow multiple physical functions (PFs) on the same "
"chip to share a devlink instance for chip-wide operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:13
msgid ""
"Multiple PFs may reside on the same physical chip, running a single "
"firmware. Some of the resources and configurations may be shared among these "
"PFs. The shared devlink instance provides an object to pin configuration "
"knobs on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:17
msgid "There are two possible usage models:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:19
msgid ""
"The shared devlink instance is used alongside individual PF devlink "
"instances, providing chip-wide configuration in addition to per-PF "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:22
msgid ""
"The shared devlink instance is the only devlink instance, without per-PF "
"instances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:25
msgid "It is up to the driver to decide which usage model to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:27
msgid "The shared devlink instance is not backed by any struct *device*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:30
msgid "Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:33
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:35
msgid "The implementation uses:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:37
msgid ""
"**Chip identification**: PFs are grouped by chip using a driver-specific "
"identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:38
msgid ""
"**Shared instance management**: Global list of shared instances with "
"reference counting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:41
msgid "API Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:43
msgid ""
"The following functions are provided for managing shared devlink instances:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:45
msgid ""
"``devlink_shd_get()``: Get or create a shared devlink instance identified by "
"a string ID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:46
msgid "``devlink_shd_put()``: Release a reference on a shared devlink instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:47
msgid ""
"``devlink_shd_get_priv()``: Get private data from shared devlink instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:50
msgid "Initialization Flow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:52
msgid "**PF calls shared devlink init** during driver probe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:53
msgid ""
"**Chip identification** using driver-specific method to determine device "
"identity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:54
msgid "**Get or create shared instance** using ``devlink_shd_get()``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:56
msgid "The function looks up existing instance by identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:57
msgid ""
"If none exists, creates new instance: - Allocates and registers devlink "
"instance - Adds to global shared instances list - Increments reference count"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:62
msgid ""
"**Set nested devlink instance** for the PF devlink instance using "
"``devl_nested_devlink_set()`` before registering the PF devlink instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:66
msgid "Cleanup Flow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:68
msgid "**Cleanup** when PF is removed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:69
msgid ""
"**Call** ``devlink_shd_put()`` to release reference (decrements reference "
"count)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:70
msgid ""
"**Shared instance is automatically destroyed** when the last PF removes "
"(reference count reaches zero)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:73
msgid "Chip Identification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:75
msgid ""
"PFs belonging to the same chip are identified using a driver-specific "
"method. The driver is free to choose any identifier that is suitable for "
"determining whether two PFs are part of the same device. Examples include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:79
msgid "**PCI VPD serial numbers**: Extract from PCI VPD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:80
msgid "**Device tree properties**: Read chip identifier from device tree"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:81
msgid ""
"**Other hardware-specific identifiers**: Any unique identifier that groups "
"PFs by chip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:84
msgid "Locking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:86
msgid ""
"A global mutex (``shd_mutex``) protects the shared instances list during "
"registration/deregistration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:88
msgid ""
"Similarly to other nested devlink instance relationships, devlink lock of "
"the shared instance should be always taken after the devlink lock of PF."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:92
msgid "Reference Counting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/devlink/devlink-shared.rst:94
msgid ""
"Each shared devlink instance maintains a reference count (``refcount_t "
"refcount``). The reference count is incremented when ``devlink_shd_get()`` "
"is called and decremented when ``devlink_shd_put()`` is called. When the "
"reference count reaches zero, the shared instance is automatically destroyed."
msgstr ""
